HEADWORD: Hibiscus
<hw>Hi*bis"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., marsh mallow;
cf. Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of plants (herbs,
shrubs, or trees), some species of which have large, showy flowers. Some
species are cultivated in India for their fiber, which is used as a
substitute for hemp. See <er>Althea</er>, <er>Hollyhock</er>, and
<er>Manoe</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

